2026-04-14 07:46:03,106 INFO RLM iteration 2/50
Reasoning: The spreadsheet has a column "A_Name" in column C (index 3) and "Entry Time" in column I (index 9).  
Column M (index 13) already holds the header "Max" and currently contains some manual results ("Latest"/"Not Latest") and many blanks.  

The task is to fill every row in column M with a formula that:
1. Looks at the Name in column C and the Entry Time in column I of the same row.  
2. Finds the latest (maximum) Entry Time for that Name across the whole sheet.  
3. Returns **"Latest"** if the row’s Entry Time equals that maximum, otherwise **"Not Latest"**.

Excel 2013 does not have `MAXIFS`, so we use an array‑formula style `MAX(IF(...))`.  
LibreOffice Calc can evaluate such an array formula without the curly‑brace syntax when entered as a normal formula; the calculation engine will treat the inner `IF` as an array automatically.

The formula to write (for row r) is:

```
=IF(Ir=MAX(IF($C$2:$C$1000=$Cr,$I$2:$I$1000)),"Latest","Not Latest")
```

We will write this formula into every cell of column M from row 2 to the last data row (`ws.max_row`).  
After saving, we will call `recalculate()` on the output file, reload it with `data_only=True`, and print a few sample results to confirm the formula works.
Code:
```repl
import openpyxl
from openpyxl.utils import get_column_letter
import os

# Paths
input_path = "/sandbox/input/input_spreadsheet/1_58723_init.xlsx"
output_dir = "/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet/"
os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)
output_path = os.path.join(output_dir, "1_58723_init.xlsx")

# Load workbook
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path)
ws = wb[wb.sheetnames[0]]  # assume first sheet

max_row = ws.max_row
max_col = ws.max_column

# Column indices (1‑based)
col_name = 3   # C = A_Name
col_time = 9   # I = Entry Time
col_target = 13  # M = Max (output)

# Write formula for each data row
for r in range(2, max_row + 1):
    # Build formula string for this row
    formula = f'=IF(I{r}=MAX(IF($C$2:$C${max_row}=$C{r},$I$2:$I${max_row})),"Latest","Not Latest")'
    ws.cell(row=r, column=col_target).value = formula

# Save to output location
wb.save(output_path)

# Recalculate formulas
from __future__ import annotations
await recalculate(output_path)

# Reload with data_only to view evaluated results
wb2 = openpyxl.load_workbook(output_path, data_only=True)
ws2 = wb2[wb2.sheetnames[0]]

# Print a few rows to verify
print("Sample evaluated results (row, Name, Entry Time, Max column):")
for r in range(2, min(7, max_row + 1)):
    name = ws2.cell(row=r, column=col_name).value
    time = ws2.cell(row=r, column=col_time).value
    status = ws2.cell(row=r, column=col_target).value
    print(r, name, time, status)

# Also check the last few rows where column was previously empty
print("Last rows:")
for r in range(max_row-4, max_row+1):
    name = ws2.cell(row=r, column=col_name).value
    time = ws2.cell(row=r, column=col_time).value
    status = ws2.cell(row=r, column=col_target).value
    print(r, name, time, status)
